Gausss Divergence Theorem (GaussOstrogradsky Theorem)
1. Statement of the Theorem
Gausss divergence theorem states that:
In words:
The total outward ux of a vector eld through a closed surface equals the volume integral of the
divergence of that vector eld over the volume enclosed by the surface.
2. Physical Signicance
LHS Net ux leaving the closed surface
RHS Total source strength inside the volume
Shows that divergence is ux per unit volume

1. Statement of Stokes Theorem
Stokes theorem states that:
In words:
The line integral (circulation) of a vector eld around a closed curve equals the surface integral of
the curl of the vector eld over any surface bounded by that curve.

vector eld
closed boundary curve
any surface bounded by
line element along
surface area element
Orientation rule:
Direction of and are related by the right-hand rule.

LHS total circulation around a loop
RHS sum of local rotations (curl) over the surface
Shows that curl represents circulation per unit area

1. Magnetic Dipole Basic Idea
A magnetic dipole is a system that produces a magnetic eld similar to that of a bar magnet, having a
north and south pole.
Examples:
Bar magnet
Current-carrying circular loop
A current loop behaves like a magnetic dipole.
2. Why a Current Loop Acts as a Magnetic Dipole
A current-carrying loop produces a magnetic eld pattern similar to a bar magnet.
One face of the loop behaves as a north pole and the other as a south pole.
Direction of poles is given by the right-hand rule.
Right-hand rule:
Curl the ngers of the right hand in the direction of current thumb gives direction of magnetic dipole
moment (north pole direction).

6. Physical Explanation

3. No torque in a uniform magnetic eld
